2017	[(S3.pi.1) Flat base change of $\Gamma$ for proper schemes]
2018	  \label{lem:S3_pi_1_Gamma_baseChange_iso_tensor_of_proper}
2019	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Gamma_baseChange_iso_tensor_of_proper}
2020	  Let $X$ be a proper scheme over a field $k$, and let $K / k$ be a field extension. Then the canonical comparison map
2021	  \[
2022	    \Gamma(X, \mathcal O_X) \otimes_k K \;\xrightarrow{\;\sim\;}\; \Gamma(X_K, \mathcal O_{X_K})
2023	  \]
2024	  is an isomorphism of $K$-algebras, where $X_K := X \times_{\Spec k} \Spec K$ is the base change of $X$ along $\Spec K \to \Spec k$. This is the specialisation of ``cohomology along proper morphisms commutes with flat base change'' (Stacks Tag~\textbf{02KH}) to the $H^0 = \Gamma$ row.
